  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH responses to vulnerable out-of-camp South Sudanese Refugees and host community in White Nile</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at supporting vulnerable out-of-camp South Sudanese Refugees (SSRs) and Host Communities (HCs) by providing sanitation and hygiene services, including school WASH facility provision in Kosti and Rabak localities in White Nile state.
Main project activities:
- Undertake Community Led Total Sanitation (CLTS) program in 25 village in Rabak locality; Pre-triggering and assessment exercise by CLTS trained facilitators for 25 communities; Triggering exercise by CLTS trained facilitators for 25 communities; Follow up visits (regular follow up visits conducted by state and locality teams); Joint ODF verification and certification visits by SMOH and CAFOD and SIDO; ODF celebration and certification.
- Construct 6 blocks (one block having four pits) of latrines in six schools (Alingaz, Alamal, Dabat Alganha, Block 29 East, Block 30 and Alhilalgdeda) primary schools.
- Conduct one 5-day TOT training on CHAST for the 24 target schoolteachers drawn from the 6 schools (4 teachers from each school). The teachers will thereafter train the students and support them to form school Hygiene Clubs.
- Undertake 5-day trainings for 250 community leader and hygiene promotors drawn from the 25 communities, the 250 trainees will be trained in 8 groups each group have 30 persons.</narrative>
  </description>
